	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_603022">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_603022">It does, and that's always been my argument against a build like this. I do, however, make sure to retain scorch and incinerate which do a lot for sustained dps instead of going for things like impact which increases your pvping ability. there are raid-end advantages to having it as well.<br />
<br />
presence of mind is just plain better than combustion for dealing damage, if not efficiency. combust doubles spell damage every 5 minutes, and presence gives you a free spell every 3 minutes. each does the same bonus basically, but pom gives it nearly twice as fast. it's also good in pvp. on clears, it means dropping in an instant pyroblast, which isn't terribly effective to combustion up in groups because the spell casts so slow.<br />
<br />
arcane power + pom is very good on bosses, and AP on AEing. a boss fight which lasts 50 seconds sees: POM, arcane power, pyroblast, fireblast, etc etc occur right in the middle of it. when AEing, AP gives you a pain 35% damage increase. that's a lot! the whelps that are bugging out on onyxia(they were in beta) are vicious AEs, as are the fire spawns and minidemons in MC. AEing through BRS with 3 groups is a good, clean way to quickly do it.<br />
<br />
to be brief, 15% mana cast through on 65 mana/tick with 50% downtime means about as much as 3pts in fire power when your mana is really being strained. so, all is not lost in terms of sustained dps.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
