</div>
<br />
My build's in another thread here, feel free to look it over. I'm not saying it's 100% right for a fire mage, but it's one idea.<br />
<br />
You'll want ignite for sure, it's a noticeable jump in dps. It's not just 40%, since it kicks off every time you crit, and the 40% applies to the crit amount. If you get down the tree to fire power, I'm told the crit applies after fire power is added in. The fire tree talents work this way, they build on each other. Critical mass will help you get more crits, which will help trigger Ignite even more often.<br />
<br />
If you're going to spend 20 in arcane, I'd suggest taking 2 points from Arcane Meditation and putting them in Improved Counterspell. Even in a PvE environment, being able to silence NPC casters is golden. I've been fighting bloodsail casters recently, and it's so funny to hit them with counterspell and have them run up and try to beat me with a melee weapon while I nuke them down. <br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				
If someone could prove to me that Ice was really really beneficial for PvE, wouldn't get my butt kicked due to its lack of dmg, then I'd do it, but I prefer fire. <br />
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
Ice is absolutely viable. Jonas is an ice mage, and there are threads about his solo AE exploits around here that are entertaining reading. The benefit of ice is absolute control over the situation. Your target is nearly always either stopped or moving very slowly, and so the danger to yourself is greatly reduced. Ice mages my level can kill things I can't kill (i.e. elites, higher level mobs, etc), but the things I can kill, I kill much faster (AE notwithstanding, I get way too much lag to do that safely).</div>
